Ghana’s Currency Strengthens to 1.5135 Against the Dollar

-- B y   J a s o n   M c L u r e
-- 
2011-04-18T14:56:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/ghana-s-currency-strengthens-to-1-5135-against-the-dollar.html
Ghana ’s currency, the cedi,
appreciated to 1.5135 against the dollar as of 2:14 p.m. in
Accra, the capital of the world’s second-biggest cocoa producer.  The currency rose 0.1 percent after closing at 1.5145 on
April 15, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason McLure in Accra at 
 jmclure@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 